Students Discover Future
*
Is Objective of Placement Ofﬁce
By Karen robinson
“We’re in the business of selling opportunities." said Zeke
Bequeira, director of Grinnell’s
Placement Office.
The Placement Office is designed to aid students in making vocational plans. It was set
up as a separate office just
over a year ago with Sequeira
as director.
One of Sequeira’s innovations
has been the Placement Office
bulletin distributed every week.
It contains summer employment information, dates of tests
and visits of industrial recruiting, and graduate fellowship
news.
He said, “We had no idea
this would flooring as it has.
We published a special bulletin
about the Peace Corps senior
program which was distributed
only to seniors and within an
hour after its distribution we
had other students calling and
coming in to ask for copies of
their own."
The Placement Office, according to Sequeira, acts as a
connector, advisor, and “brown
en" It brings together recruiting and job seekers, but more
than that it “seeks to find
means by which students can
translate their educational experiences into productive and
exciting locations,”
”Most students seem to ignore vocational planning during their understand years, and
by their senior year it is sometimes too late. How many students, for example, choose a
major with a thoroughly investigated location in mind, or
perhaps more important, how
often do they select their work
in supporting disciplines with
a direction in View? Often the
related course work can do
much to enhance a person’s lap
for value,” said Sequeira.
He continued, “This is like
buying the most beautiful Cadillac you can find and then letting it sit because you won’t
spend anything on gasoline,
service, and licensing. Students
and their families often sacrifice a great deal for a BA, but
area’t willing to invest a little
time and energy in investigation what they want of the world
and what the World wants of
them."
information is available in
quantity at the Placement office. Industry actively reprints
college graduates and puts vocational information at the disposal of colleges. The federal
 
